My bad - Huawei Y70, not Vivo. The steps are basically the same though since both run Android.

*For Huawei Y70, 2 key differences:*

*1. Finding your IP on Huawei Y70:*
`Settings` → `Wi-Fi` → tap the WiFi name you're connected to → scroll down → you'll see `IP address`. Looks like `192.168.1.45`

*2. Termux install on Huawei* 
Huawei blocks Google Play sometimes, so grab Termux from F-Droid: http://f-droid.org → search "Termux". Play Store version on Huawei often has issues.

*3. Huawei "Battery Optimization" will kill your server* 
This is the big one. Huawei phones are aggressive with killing background apps. After you start the server in Termux:
`Settings` → `Apps` → `Apps` → `Termux` → `Battery` → set to `Don't allow` / `Unrestricted` 
Also lock Termux in Recent Apps so it doesn't get swiped away.

Then the http://Node.js commands I sent before will work:
pkg install nodejs-lts
cd /sdcard/Download/Lockin  
npm start
*Reality check*: Running a server 24/7 on a Huawei Y70 will overheat + drain battery fast. It's fine for quick testing with 2 phones, but don't expect it to stay up for hours.

